-- MTN Says Subscribers Advanced 3.7% to 170.6 Million in March
-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 2012-05-04T11:01:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-04/mtn-says-subscribers-advanced-3-7-to-170-6-million-in-march.html
MTN Group Ltd. (MTN) , Africa’s largest
mobile-phone company, said subscriptions rose 3.7 percent in the
first quarter as users were attracted to its data packages and
mobile banking facilities.  MTN had 170.6 million subscribers at the end of March,
compared with 164.5 million at the end of December, the
Johannesburg-based company said today. In Nigeria, the company’s
biggest market, it added 1.26 million new customers while  South
Africa  contributed 3.2 percent more users, MTN said.  The Iranian unit “continued to deliver a solid performance
growing its subscriber base by 6.2 percent and increasing its
share of the market,” MTN said.  The group had 6.2 million subscribers using its Mobile
Money banking product by the end of March, which is now active
in 13 of the company’s 22 markets in  Africa  and the  Middle East .
Data products, including text messages, contribute 14.4 percent
to group revenue, mainly at the South African unit.  MTN said it expects 21.3 million net new customers in 2012,
compared with a December estimate of 20.3 million.  To contact the reporter on this story: Sikonathi Mantshantsha in
Johannesburg at   smantshantsh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story: Kenneth Wong
at   kwong11@bloomberg.net  